Alannah Hill was diagnosed with an invasive malignant melanoma . 
  The Tasmanian-born designer has had part of her toe removed and a skin graft from her inner thigh . 
  She has a 'very good' prognosis and is taking three months off to recuperate . 
  Her doctor told her to get her freckle checked after she broke her foot . 
  Hill said she is speaking out to warn others about skin cancer . 
 